# modular-polynomial data (phi_files/).  A 46 MB subset is bundled via git add -f
# (see phi_files_manifest.txt): for EVERY class-invariant family, the modular
# polynomials Phi_{l,f} for l <= 71 (enumeration) plus the invariant->j polynomial
# Psi_f; the classical Phi_l (the phi_j_* files) are included on the same rule --
# they are needed at the primes dividing the LEVEL of the chosen invariant (e.g.
# phi_j_59 for Atkin A_59) to derive the starting f-value from the starting
# j-invariant, not for enumeration.  The full ~2.2 GB database (all levels) is NOT
# redistributed -- see INSTALL.  Missing files degrade gracefully (oneshot skips
# that discriminant and tries the next winner).
phi_files/*

